LongDescription = <div class="col-sm-7 col-xs-12 left-col">
    <p>
    The UCS Intercom Service (ICS) is a backend service that acts as an intermediary for the
    secure communication and Single Sign-On between other services. The ICS allows webservice
    backends to communicate with each other based on the Single Sign-On session of the
    current end user while ensuring session security.

    The ICS is very specific for dedicated use cases, currently in the interaction between
    Open-Xchange, Nextcloud and elements/matrix. Details are outlined in the documentation.
    </p>
    
    <h3>Before installing</h3>
    <p>
        Make sure to place your secrets inside this files:
        <ul>
            <li>/etc/intercom-client.secret</li>
            <li>/etc/intercom.secret</li>
            <li>/etc/matrix.secret</li>
            <li>/etc/intercom-portal.secret</li>
        </ul>
    </p>
    </div>
